   "source": [
    "# Brick element Response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Supported Brick elements include most brick elements in OpenSees, including:\n",
    "\n",
    "- ✅ stdBrick\n",
    "- ✅ bbarBrick\n",
    "- ✅ Brick20N\n",
    "- ✅ SSPbrick\n",
    "- ✅ FourNodeTetrahedron\n",
    "- ✅ brickUP\n",
    "- ✅ bbarBrickUP\n",
    "- ✅ 20_8_BrickUP\n",
    "- ✅ SSPbrickUP\n",
    "- ✅ ......"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:25.949371Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:25.948371Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.619141Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.618197Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:25.949371Z"
    },

   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import openseespy.opensees as ops\n",
    "\n",
    "import opstool as opst"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "opst.load_ops_examples(\"Pier-Brick\")\n",
    "# or your model code here"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.620145Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.619141Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.331575Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.330569Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:27.620145Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# add gravity loads\n",
    "ops.timeSeries(\"Linear\", 1)\n",
    "ops.pattern(\"Plain\", 1, 1)\n",
    "_ = opst.pre.gen_grav_load(direction=\"z\", factor=-9.81)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# plot\n",
    "opst.vis.pyvista.set_plot_props(notebook=True)\n",
    "fig = opst.vis.pyvista.plot_model(show_nodal_loads=True)\n",
    "fig.show(jupyter_backend=\"static\")"
   ]

  {

   "metadata": {

    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "## Result Saving"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.333575Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.333575Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.343019Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.342010Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.333575Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Nsteps = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "ops.system(\"BandGeneral\")\n",
    "# Create the constraint handler, the transformation method\n",
    "ops.constraints(\"Transformation\")\n",
    "# Create the DOF numberer, the reverse Cuthill-McKee algorithm\n",
    "ops.numberer(\"RCM\")\n",
    "# Create the convergence test, the norm of the residual with a tolerance of\n",
    "# 1e-12 and a max number of iterations of 10\n",
    "ops.test(\"NormDispIncr\", 1.0e-12, 10, 3)\n",
    "# Create the solution algorithm, a Newton-Raphson algorithm\n",
    "ops.algorithm(\"Newton\")\n",
    "# Create the integration scheme, the LoadControl scheme using steps of 0.1\n",
    "ops.integrator(\"LoadControl\", 1 / Nsteps)\n",
    "# Create the analysis object\n",
    "ops.analysis(\"Static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "``opstool`` allows us to save the data at each step of the analysis!\n",
    "First, we create a database class using :class:`opstool.post.CreateODB`, and then, during each step of the analysis, we call its method ``.fetch_response_step`` to retrieve the data for the current step. \n",
    "Once all the analysis steps are completed, we use the ``.save_response`` method to save the data in one go."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "``compute_mechanical_measures`` is used to compute the mechanical measures, including various stress and strain measures.\n",
    "\n",
    "``project_gauss_to_nodes`` is used to project the Gauss point results to the nodes.\n",
    "\n",
    "* \"copy\": The response of each node is copied from the Gaussian point closest to it.\n",
    "* \"average\": The response of each node is equal to the weighted average of the responses of all Gaussian points of the element, with the weight being the integration point weight.\n",
    "* \"extrapolate\": The nodal responses are obtained by extrapolating the element shape functions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.346023Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.345024Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.765613Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.765613Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.346023Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  All responses data with _odb_tag = <span style=\"color: #008080; text-decoration-color: #008080; font-weight: bold\">1</span> saved in \n",
       "<span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">g:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #ce181e; text-decoration-color: #ce181e; font-weight: bold\">zarr</span>!\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  All responses data with _odb_tag = \u001b[1;36m1\u001b[0m saved in \n",
       "\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30mg:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;206;24;30mzarr\u001b[0m!\n"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ODB = opst.post.CreateODB(\n",
    "    odb_tag=1,\n",
    "    compute_mechanical_measures=True,\n",
    "    project_gauss_to_nodes=\"copy\",  # \"extrapolate\", \"copy\", \"average\"\n",
    "    nd_material_type=\"brittle\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "for i in range(Nsteps):\n",
    "    # Perform the analysis step\n",
    "    ops.analyze(1)\n",
    "    # fetch the response step, every 10 steps for reducing the size of the ODB file\n",
    "    if (i + 1) % 10 == 0:\n",
    "        ODB.fetch_response_step()\n",
    "    # ODB.fetch_response_step()   # or every step\n",
    "ODB.save_response()  # save the response to a file"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Result Reading"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "raw_mimetype": "text/restructuredtext",
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""

     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "The provided function :func:`opstool.post.get_element_responses` make it easy to read element responses.\n",
    "\n",
    "``ele_type=\"Solid\"`` is used to specify extracting the response of solid elements."
   ]

   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {

    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.766615Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.766615Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.831518Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.831518Z",
     "shell.execute_reply.started": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.766615Z"
    },
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<pre style=\"white-space:pre;overflow-x:auto;line-height:normal;font-family:Menlo,'DejaVu Sans Mono',consolas,'Courier New',monospace\"><span style=\"color: #cf6275; text-decoration-color: #cf6275; font-weight: bold\">OPSTOOL</span> <span style=\"color: #12e193; text-decoration-color: #12e193; font-weight: bold\">::</span>  Loading Solid response data from <span style=\"color: #2dde98; text-decoration-color: #2dde98; font-weight: bold\">g:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-</span><span style=\"color: #2dde98; text-decoration-color: #2dde98; font-weight: bold\">1.</span><span style=\"color: #2dde98; text-decoration-color: #2dde98; font-weight: bold\">zarr</span> <span style=\"color: #808000; text-decoration-color: #808000\">...</span>\n",
       "</pre>\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "\u001b[1;38;2;207;98;117mOPSTOOL\u001b[0m \u001b[1;38;2;18;225;147m::\u001b[0m  Loading Solid response data from \u001b[1;38;2;45;222;152mg:\\opstool\\docs\\src\\post\\.opstool.output/RespStepData-\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;45;222;152m1.\u001b[0m\u001b[1;38;2;45;222;152mzarr\u001b[0m \u001b[33m...\u001b[0m\n"

   "source": [

  {

   "source": [
    "``Stresses`` and ``Strains`` refer to the stress and strain at the Gauss points. \n",
    "Stress and strain consist of six components aligned with the global coordinate system, as well as additional stress measures:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "['sigma11' 'sigma22' 'sigma33' 'sigma12' 'sigma23' 'sigma13']\n",
      "['eps11' 'eps22' 'eps33' 'eps12' 'eps23' 'eps13']\n",
      "['p1' 'p2' 'p3' 'tau_max']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(all_resp.stressDOFs.data)\n",
    "print(all_resp.strainDOFs.data)\n",
    "print(all_resp.measures.data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Although we analyzed 100 steps, we saved the data every 10 steps, so we only have data for 10 steps, and the time corresponds accordingly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

   "source": [
    "Below, we retrieve the stress and strain data, which is a **4D** array.\n",
    "The dimensions are, in order, **('time', 'eleTags', 'GaussPoints', 'DOFs')**, and we can conveniently retrieve data based on these dimensions and their coordinates."
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   ]

    "editable": true,
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2024-11-22T02:28:29.898332Z",

    "gauss_points = stresses2.coords[\"GaussPoints\"].data"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [

    "    s = stresses2.sel(GaussPoints=gp_no)\n",
    "    time = s.coords[\"time\"].data\n",
    "    plt.plot(time, s, label=f\"GP{gp_no}\")\n",

    "plt.xlabel(\"Time\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Stress\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also compute averages along a specific dimension. For example, below, we calculate the average stress at the Gauss points:"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],

    "plt.title(\"Mean stress-time curve: max shear stress\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Time\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Stress\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
